Vietnam’s Equity Movers: Hoa An Joint-Stock, Phu Nhuan Jewelry

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-10-13T05:33:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-13/vietnam-s-equity-movers-hoa-an-joint-stock-phu-nhuan-jewelry.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in  Vietnam  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in  Ho Chi Minh City .  The VN Index, the benchmark measure of the Ho Chi Minh City
Stock Exchange, rose for the first day in three, climbing 0.4
percent to 412.59.  Hoa An Joint-Stock Co. (DHA VN), a mining and road-building
company, advanced 1.7 percent to 12,200 dong. The Dong Nai-based
company will pay its investors a dividend of 1,000 dong a share
this quarter, Hoa An said in a filing on the exchange’s website,
without giving a date for the payment.  Phu Nhuan Jewelry Joint-Stock Co. (PNJ VN), Vietnam’s only
listed jewelry manufacturer, gained for a second day, adding 2.2
percent to a three-day high of 37,200 dong. Gold advanced for a
second day on speculation Slovakia will approve  Europe ’s
enhanced bailout fund.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Shiyin Chen at 
 schen37@bloomberg.net  